                <h3>1. San Diego</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">San Diego is the largest city in the southern part of California. The town is famous for beaches, tourism, naval operations, and swimming. The place is also a central hub for telecommunications, biotechnology, and defense industries. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">San Diego has a diverse culture and Mexican influence due to its close location to the border. The primary source of attraction in San Diego is the beach. Make sure to visit the beach towns like Ocean Beach and La Jolla. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">You can visit Balboa Park, which is a 1200-acre urban park. It is famous for its world-class zoo and cultivated restful areas. The USS Midway Museum, the longest-serving aircraft in the world, has been shifted to San Diego. You will get a chance to get involved, test the simulators, climb the cockpits and watch documentary films on the events that took place. </p>

                <h3>2. South Lake Tahoe</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">South Lake Tahoe is one of the largest lakes in the world and is situated between California and Nevada. The Lake is the best place for skiing, snowboarding, snowshoeing, and snowmobiling in the winters. During summers, visitors can enjoy outdoor activities. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">These include sailing, kayaking, mountain biking, and swimming which is the best thing on the Lake. The city is small and is geared towards tourism. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">The Heavenly Gondola is one of the best places to visit in California. The Gondola ride will give you one of the most exquisite views of the surrounding mountains and the Lake. You can also go for a hike on Rubicon Trail. The dramatic rock formations and the stunning views of the Lake's turquoise water will shock you. </p>

                <h3>3. Monterey</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">Even Though Monterey is not a popular tourist destination, it is still a beautiful example of a coastal town. The city has a rich heritage and rugged landscapes. The city is an excellent stop for history buffs and art lovers. Kayaking, bird watching, whale watching, parasailing, and hang gliding are some of the best things to do in the city of Monterey. Tourists can also visit several art galleries, museums, and the famous Laguna Seca Raceway. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">The Monterey Bay Aquarium has an exhibit of more than 43, which displays various marine lives. The Monterey State Historic Park is also known as the walking path of history. The course contains dozens of different buildings and gives an extraordinary view. It is one of the most fun Monterey attractions. </p>

                <h3>4. Napa</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">The city of Napa is known for its world-class wineries and vineyards. You can tour vineyards' fields and explore them alone or with an organized group. The town is great to try out the bed and breakfast lodging, and you must try the exquisite cuisines made by renowned chefs. You can bike through the winding vineyard roads and explore several different wineries. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">Wine enthusiasts should also try checking out neighboring Sonoma County, best known for winemaking. Downtown Napa is incomplete without your visit to the riverfront and veterans park. You can get a beautiful view of ducks and kayaks to paddle together in the water. The vine trail offers a wide path that is enough for bicyclists and walkers. </p>

                <h3>5. Death Valley</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">The city of Death Valley is one of the hottest, driest, and lowest places on the planet. Therefore one must give it a try during their stay in California. The landscapes are varied; you can see snow-capped mountains, rolling sand dunes, parched salt flats, and luscious forests. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">The Valley has some sites worth watching. The Zabriskie Point, the Wild rose Charcoal Kilns, and the ghost towns are among them. You can use the Death Valley Junction to explore various sites. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">You can hike in the deep canyons to salt flats, sand dunes, and desert peaks. Hence it is considered a hikers paradise. Death Valley offers several campgrounds. Hundreds of miles of dirt roads provide excellent roads for mountain biking. </p>

                <h3>6. Los Angeles</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">When people make their trip to California, the first thing that pops up in their minds is Los Angeles and Hollywood. Los Angeles has beautiful weather throughout the year. You might notice many sights in movies and TV shows. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">Downtown is the center of a thriving business and arts district. Beverly Hills is a famous shopping district. You should also check out the Sunset Strip music clubs, the beachfront Santa Monica promenade, and the famous Venice Boardwalk. To explore more of the city, you can hire a travel guide. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">The Getty Centre is the most impressive architectural achievement in the United States. The museum contains some of the best fine works of art. Zuma Beach is the best beach spot for sunbathing and swimming. Therefore, it is one of the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/blog/explore-california-top-cities-to-travel-in-2022.aspx">best cities to visit in California</a>.</p>

                <h3>7. Sacramento</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">Sacramento City is not only known for its government offices. The city provides plenty of things to do for its visitors. It is one of the top art cities with museums, architecture, and galleries. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">This will surely satisfy any art lover. You can try checking out a theater performance or a comedy show during your visit. Try to spend quality time in Midtown which has modern restaurants, bars, and boutique shops. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">The Crocker Museum has all kinds of ideas and mediums to be examined. There are pieces in this museum from Asia, Europe, and Africa. The Old Sacramento Historic Park offers visitors an invaluable history lesson. The district thrives in business and has beautiful establishments. It is a lovely spot for people who love uncovering history. </p>

                <h3>8. Fresno</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">Fresno is the largest city and provides easy access to Yosemite National Park. Fresno provides an excellent home base for travelers who want to check out Yosemite and Sequoia National Park. Fresno gives you an idea of how important agriculture is to the state of California. The most prominent farming area in the US is the Central Valley. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">You can visit the Woodward Regional Park, which spreads over 300 acres. It is filled with modern amenities and has unique spots. You will love the beautiful sightseeing views. The Fresno Art Museum is one of the top spots in the city for art and artistic expression. </p>
                <h3>9. Mt Shasta</h3>
